## Lookup arguments

Specify exactly one of:

| argument | behavior |
|---|---|
| `id` | Direct lookup by integer ID. |
| `name` | Exact-match lookup by name (fuzzy server search, then exact `name ==` filter). Errors if zero or more than one destination matches. |

## Returned values

| attribute | description |
|---|---|
| `id` | Log destination integer ID. |
| `name` | Destination name. |
| `enabled` | Whether the destination is enabled. |
| `type` | `syslog` or `webhook`. |
| `streams` | Set of forwarded streams: `security`, `policy`, `api`, `app`. |
| `min_severity` | One of `info`, `low`, `medium`, `high`, `critical`. |
| `config` | Per-type config JSON (sensitive). **Webhook auth secrets are masked as `****`** in this read — they cannot be recovered from the data source. |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp. |
| `updated_at` | Last update timestamp. |

For the full shape of `config` per `type` (syslog and webhook fields, the webhook
`auth` variants, and which fields are secret), see the
[`mistershell_log_destination` resource](../resources/log_destination.md) page.
